trans-unit.source: Provides a regular expression to parse the opening tag of an HTML element, an XML element, or an ASP.NET Web server control tag, for applications that target the [!INCLUDE[net_v35SP1_short](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] and earlier versions.

The TagRegex35 class provides a regular expression that ASP.NET uses internally to parse the opening tag of an HTML element, an XML element, or an ASP.NET Web server control tag, for applications that target the [!INCLUDE[net_v35SP1_short](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] and earlier versions.

ASP.NET uses the <xref:System.Web.RegularExpressions.TagRegex?displayProperty=fullName> class for applications that target the [!INCLUDE[net_v40_short](~/add/includes/net-v40-short-md.md)] and later versions.
> [!NOTE] > The <xref:System.Web.RegularExpressions> classes are used internally by the .NET Framework to parse ASP.NET pages.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.RegularExpressions.TagRegex35"></xref> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.RegularExpressions.TagRegex35"></xref> class with a specified time-out value.

The `A_1` parameter represents the maximum time interval during which the regular expression engine tries to find a match before the operation times out and a <xref:System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexMatchTimeoutException> exception is thrown.
A time-out interval, or <xref:System.Text.RegularExpressions.Regex.InfiniteMatchTimeout?displayProperty=fullName> if matching operations should not time out.
